kish) origin, derived from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, displacing the Old English form <i>Æþelbeorht</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Maredudd \"Hir\" ap Rhys was born about 1180, in Wales, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Goleubryd ferch John."},"et":{"about 1180–":"umbes 1180–Surnud","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","about 1180":"umbes 1180","1200":"1200","1180":"1180","Wales":"Wales","of, Meisgyn commote, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","of,,Deheubarth,Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1180–":"noin 1180–Kuollut","1180–Female":"1180–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","about 1180":"noin 1180","1200":"1200","1180":"1180","Wales":"Wales","of, Meisgyn commote, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of,,Deheubarth,Wales":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1180–":"environ 1180–Décédé","1180–Female":"1180–Décédée","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1180–Male":"1180–Décédé","about 1180":"environ 1180","1200":"1200","1180":"1180","Wales":"Galles","of, Meisgyn commote, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Glamorgan, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","of,,Deheubarth,Wales":"Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Maredudd \"Hir\" ap Rhys est né environ 1180, à Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Goleubryd ferch John."},"de":{"about 1180–":"um 1180–Verstorben","1180–Female":"1180–Verstorben","1200–Male":"1200–Verstorben","1180–Male":"1180–Verstorben","about 1180":"um 1180","1200":"1200","1180":"1180","Wales